Package: kdetoys-kde3
Architecture: all
Section: kde
Depends: amor-kde3 (>= ${Source-Version}), eyesapplet-kde3 (>= ${Source-Version}), fifteenapplet-kde3 (>= ${Source-Version}), kmoon-kde3 (>= ${Source-Version}), kodo-kde3 (>= ${Source-Version}), kteatime-kde3 (>= ${Source-Version}), ktux-kde3 (>= ${Source-Version}), kweather-kde3 (>= ${Source-Version}), kworldclock-kde3 (>= ${Source-Version})
Suggests: kdetoys-kde3-doc-html (>= ${Source-Version})
Description: toys from the official KDE3 release
 KDE (the K Desktop Environment) is a powerful Open Source graphical
 desktop environment for Unix workstations. It combines ease of use,
 contemporary functionality, and outstanding graphical design with the
 technological superiority of the Unix operating system.
 .
 This metapackage includes a collection of toys and fun extras provided
 with the official release of KDE3.

Package: kdetoys-kde3-doc-html
Architecture: all
Section: doc
Suggests: konqueror-kde3 | www-browser, kdetoys-kde3
Replaces: amor-kde3 (<< 4:2.2.0-0), kmoon-kde3 (<< 4:2.2.0-0), kodo-kde3 (<< 4:2.2.0-0), kteatime-kde3 (<< 4:2.2.0-0), kweather-kde3 (<< 4:3.0.0-0), kworldclock-kde3 (<< 4:2.2.0-0)
Description: KDE3 toys documentation in HTML format
 By default the modules provided by KDE only provide their documentation
 in KDE docbook format, which can only be read by Konqueror or KHelpCenter.
 This package provides all of the KDE toys documentation converted to
 HTML format so it can be read with any web browser.
 .
 The documentation will be installed into the usual directories
 /opt/kde3/share/doc/kde/HTML/<language>/<app>/, for instance
 /opt/kde3/share/doc/kde/HTML/en/amor/. Documentation is provided for most
 KDE toys packages.
 .
 This package is part of KDE3, and a component of the KDE toys module.
 See the 'kde-kde3' and 'kdetoys-kde3' packages for more information.

Package: amor-kde3
Architecture: any
Section: games
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Recommends: kwin-kde3
Suggests: khelpcenter-kde3
Conflicts: task-kdetoys-kde3
Replaces: kdetoys-kde3 (<< 4:3.0.1-0), task-kdetoys-kde3
Description: a KDE3 creature for your desktop
 AMOR stands for Amusing Misuse Of Resources. It provides several different
 characters who prance around your X screen doing tricks and giving you tips.
 .
 Note that AMOR will only work with some window managers. Both KWin (the
 KDE window manager) and Metacity (a GTK2 window manager) are supported.
 .
 This package is part of KDE3, and a component of the KDE toys module.
 See the 'kde-kde3' and 'kdetoys-kde3' packages for more information.

