Package: kweather-kde3
Architecture: any
Section: kde
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Recommends: kicker-kde3
Suggests: khelpcenter-kde3
Description: weather display applet for KDE3
 An applet for the KDE panel that displays your area's current weather.
 Information shown includes the temperature, wind speed, air pressure
 and more. By pressing a button a full weather report can be obtained.
 .
 KWeather also provides a weather service that can track multiple weather
 stations and provide this information to other applications, including
 Konqueror's sidebar and Kontact's summary page.
 .
 This package is part of KDE3, and a component of the KDE toys module.
 See the 'kde-kde3' and 'kdetoys-kde3' packages for more information.

Package: kworldclock-kde3
Architecture: any
Section: games
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Suggests: kdeartwork-misc-kde3, kicker-kde3, kdesktop-kde3, khelpcenter-kde3
Conflicts: task-kdetoys-kde3, kworldwatch-kde3 (<= 4:2.2-beta1-1)
Replaces: kdetoys-kde3 (<< 4:3.0.1-0), task-kdetoys-kde3, kworldwatch-kde3 (<= 4:2.2-beta1-1)
Provides: kworldwatch-kde3
Description: earth watcher for KDE3
 Displays where in the world it is light and dark depending on time, as
 well as offering the time in all of the major cities of the world.
 This can be run standalone, as an applet in the KDE panel or as a
 desktop background.
 .
 Additional kworldclock themes are available in the kdeartwork-misc package.
 .
 This package is part of KDE3, and a component of the KDE toys module.
 See the 'kde-kde3' and 'kdetoys-kde3' packages for more information.

Package: kdetoys-kde3-dbg
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Depends: kdelibs-kde3-dbg
Priority: extra
Description: debugging symbols for kdetoys-kde3
 This package contains the debugging symbols associated with kdetoys-kde3.
 They will automatically be used by gdb for debugging kdetoys-related
 issues.
